      "message": "This is primarily to solve the struggle of naming things in the codebase.\n`Res` suffix worked fine so far but in a future CL I\u0027ll add an promise base observable that is not a server response.\n\nThis is somewhat consistent with the allowed usage of $ suffix in\nhttps://g3doc.corp.google.com/javascript/typescript/g3doc/styleguide.md?cl\u003dhead#naming-style\n\nThough, in our case:\n1. All attributes are observables by default, and do not have any special suffix.\n2. All promise based observables have $ suffix.\n",
